### .NET version

.NET 11 (and every shipped release back to the initial WinForms source import in commit `195f89af7`).

### Did it work in .NET Framework?

Not tested/verified

### Did it work in any of the earlier releases of .NET Core or .NET 5+?

No. The line was added in the initial WinForms source import (`195f89af7`, "Added System.Windows.Forms source") and has not been modified since (only a path move in `17fd2a33ec`).

### Issue description

`PropertyGrid.ResetHelpForeColor` calls `_helpPane.ResetBackColor()` instead of `_helpPane.ResetForeColor()`:

```csharp
// src/System.Windows.Forms/System/Windows/Forms/Controls/PropertyGrid/PropertyGrid.cs:3631
private void ResetHelpForeColor() => _helpPane.ResetBackColor();
```



### Steps to reproduce

Direct invocation (no public-API repro exists):

```csharp
using PropertyGrid grid = new();
grid.HelpForeColor = Color.Red;
grid.HelpBackColor = Color.Yellow;

grid.TestAccessor.Dynamic.ResetHelpForeColor();

// Expected: HelpForeColor == SystemColors.ControlText, HelpBackColor == Color.Yellow
// Actual:   HelpForeColor == Color.Red,                HelpBackColor == SystemColors.Control
